DEPUTIES SEEK IDENTITY OF SLAIN LATINO MAN 
Sheriff's deputies Saturday worked to learn the identity of a Latino man found 
shot to death on Domingo Avenue in San Juan Capistrano. 
Lt. Jay Mendez said the body of the unidentified man was discovered shortly 
after 9 p.m. Friday near the Capistrano Beach post office. He said the man had 
been shot several times in the head. 
Authorities said deputies were seeking several men who had been seen in the 
area at about the time of the shooting, and were also looking for anyone who 
may have witnessed it. 
